reviews.review_text: Raw and unforgettable... By far my favorite Dick's Picks and the most memorable show for me... and it still amazes me again and again...  BUY OR GET THIS SHOW!  You will not regret it.
Reviewing the artwork of late Agree on the artwork. "Steppin' Out..." is a great 4-disc set, but the cover art isn't up to par.

Saint Stephen, hiss, NRPS, Cold Rain and Snow Sounds like during one of the early gens, someone added the studio version of St Stephen up to where the live tape started recording (or was salvaged or whatever). There's hiss on the studio portion as well. I suppose it's better than missing the beginning entirely. That's something I would do for my personal listening. I would still recommend just buying the DP though. You may as well have a much cleaner copy of this great show. 

This copy would only get only 3 stars for sound quality hiss,  except it's the only copy with NRPS. So that takes it right up to 5. But while you're downloading this for the New Riders portion, get the Cold Rain and Snow from one of the better SBs since it didn't make it to the DP.

Pulled in to Nazareth.. This fills out the standard circulating recording with the addition of the NRPS set which features Jerry & Ace sitting in.
For my money THE Weight with Jerry on Pedal Steel 
as well as his distinct backing vocals is priceless.
We get more of the electric Dead Set as well.
When folks call this the best That's it for the Other One
I would focus down on the Cryptical return because 
that is meltdown intense.
And speaking of meltdown check out the Viola Lee..
